Preheat the oven to 220C/200C Fan/Gas 7.Put the salmon in a roasting dish with the oil and butter and roast for 8–10 minutes until blackened. Squeeze over the lemon juice and set aside to rest before slicing.Heat the oil in a pan and sauté the beans, red onion, garlic and chilli paste until softened. Add the lime juice and season.Mix together the dressing ingredients in a bowl and add enough hot water to make a spoonable consistency.Serve the hot smoked salmon on plates and top with the vegetables. Drizzle over the dressing and scatter over the peanuts.